<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1000" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1000">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.48/3206</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of War</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">War Department</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 21, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I beg leave to advise
                            you, with reference to a recent request of your Department that steps
                            have been taken to place the transport <hi rend="italic">Sumner</hi>,
                            now at Newport News, Virginia, in commission at once for the return of
                            refugees from Vera Cruz and Tampico, Mexico.</p>
                        <p>The crew and supplies will be placed aboard, and the ship made fully
                            ready for sea at the earliest practicable date.</p>
                        <p>The Surgeon General has been notified to provide the necessary medical
                            equipment and personnel and the Chief Signal Officer to arrange for
                            radio operators, [etc.]</p>
                        <p>Very sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Newton D. Baker</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>